op align=left class=m><span class=title> Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> Anyone notice screwup with Rampage and Heal time?<br>
Just curious, has anyone had any problem with Rampaging mobs?  Wierd things been happening on the usual mobs we kill&gt;.&lt;   Went to kill Creator in ssra after patch, he was on fire.  At the end he was rampaging more then handful of  targets.  2nd try, we had dead people &quot;relogging&quot; before res (to clear list), still had 2 cle 1 chanter 1 mage 2 war and others collapsing just because rampage at &quot;SAME&quot; time. (yes this is after cripple and zland claw in) <br>
<br>
As general knowledge I thought rampage was about 3~ targets per on high hate list.  Please correct me if I am wrong.<br>
<br>
On Cazic Thule(a wimp...) we had CT rampaging on the designated rampage takerX3 + 2 additional clerics.  Also funny thing, you get &quot;You have been healed for 5423 point&quot; THEN you get &quot;You have died&quot; 2 sec right after lol.  I thought it was lag, but happened 4 times total on different tanks...<br>
<br>
Let me know if you have similar things happening after this patch.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uranadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ranadin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/02 6:00:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> guess tigole sumed it up on los page-.-;<br>
<br>
MT being ched and dying 2 sec after been happning on almost all our raids&gt;.&lt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udurusarx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Durus Arx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/02 1:25:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> Heal sooner. If you take enough damage immediately after you're healed that you'd have died without the heal, you die. Seems to be a synch problem between the client and the servers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usanadan1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanadan1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:17:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> My question on rampage is how exactly do you control it?<br>
<br>
Tried Rhag2 late last night and I thought I had a strategy for him since he was a perma rooted mob.  Send in main tank who is being healed and then send in three rampage tanks with healers assigned for them.  It didn't work at all, the clerics were getting rampaged and we got owned.  This was my guild's first attempt at a rampaging mob and it was nasty, fun but nasty.<br>
<br>
So how do you guys set up the rampage list on a mob so that you know who is being rampaged.  Examples of how you start a fight and control rampage for various mobs would be very helpful if it's not too much information. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukanamdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanamdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:35:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Heal sooner. If you take enough damage immediately after you're healed that you'd have died without the heal, you die. Seems to be a synch problem between the client and the servers.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It's not a synchronisation problem, it's a more generalized problem.<br>
<br>
Quite simply, since the last patch, the client is utterly FUBAR regarding applying info that the server sends him.<br>
<br>
This is a common cause to all the current problems:<br>
- People getting hit by AOEs that aren't in fact hit (fake curses, mana drained that &quot;magically&quot; restores when you cast or use a right-click item)<br>
<br>
Curses for example are funny. You get hit by a debuff, your old buff is destroyed, you can get a cure<br>
which leaves you without the buff. But camp and relog, and voilà: your buff is back!<br>
<br>
- People that get a &quot;You resisted XXX&quot; message, and suffer the effects.<br>
<br>
Lots of encounters with an AOE knockback. You resist the knockback, yet fling all over.<br>
<br>
- Client counts damage reported in your HP total, but does NOT count heals (which means you're not healed until the next tick, when your current HP total is reported back).<br>
<br>
Well, that's what you see above. The trick is that the client counts all damage accrued, and none of the heals, and when you get below -10 (a holdover of AD&amp;D rules), it tells the server that you've died. Your only hope is that the client gets a summary of your current HP from the server before he thinks you died.<br>
<br>
It's all the same thing: client incorrectly parsing the protocol from the server!<br>
<br>
I sometimes regret the old whineboards. The stuff would have been soooo dissected and yelled at, you'd have been sure Verant would know about it. As it is, I'm not even sure somebody at Verant is aware of what exactly is broken in their client. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukanamdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanamdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:37:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> Oh, and you can be pretty sure that, if the client had been broken, and damage was not accrued, but heals did (letting people survive when they should die), there would have been an emergency fix in long ago <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umojak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mojak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:39:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> The way I see it<br>
