It's just that quality game making ability VI has, thats all =x <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umemnenthmoondust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Memnenth Moondust</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 9:20:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> Last nite we completely controlled the Rampage on Rhag2.<br>
<br>
As far as I can tell, it is the top 5 people on the hate list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uluxardarogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LuxarDaRogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 9:45:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> Rampage on Rhag 2 has been FUBAR'ed forever. You can wait 30 secs after everyone else engages, do like 30 points of dmg and be on the rampage list, and THEN once you are on it, you do NOT get off it again at all. (I have been rampaged.. backed off and CAMPED, came back, did another 30-40 dmg and been back on it. )<br>
<br>
So what you do is go near the exit of the room and wait as he wont rampage you that far.. really fun.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umurghkhor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>murghkhor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 10:30:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10419.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on rampage.</span><hr size=1> Rampage list is seperate from Hate list. <br>
<br>
Rampage list is based on order of engagement.<br>
<br>
When a mob rampages he hits ONE additional target (not 3 or 4) on the Rampage list.<br>
<br>
Rampage list will not remove your name till the mob is dead. You can get a CoH. You can die and get rezzed. You can zone. You will remain in your order on the Rampage list. <br>
<br>
Rampage radius is usually slightly larger than melee radius. <br>
<br>
If you are on high on rampage list but not in rampage radius, the mob will hit the next guy on the rampage list until you move back into rampage radius. <br>
<br>
Mobs will NOT move to you or try to summon you based on your position on the Rampage list, but only the hate list.<br>
<br>
Rampage radius are known to be buggy where the mob will hit you far outside the normal expected rampage radius (like across the zone).<br>
<br>
Mobs maintain rampage lists (e.g. pullers) even when hate list is clear and they stand unagroed. Even pets can get on rampage lists based on order of engagement. When they fixed it so pets stay off the hate list (and dont tank) they didnt alter rampage lists. We always have a newly sentry eat all rampages for the progenitor. Really helped when we killed him first time with 8 ppl. I'm pretty sure that if the pet dies the owner is on the rampage list next, forgot.<br>
<br>
It's easy to control rampages. Make the FIRST guy to get hit by a rampage stay in rampage radius and keep him healed. He can do no dmg to the mob if he/she likes. He will continue to take all ramgages. <br>
<br>
Clerics / Healers tend to get high on rampage lists if they throw one fast heal on the MT right after MT engages. Then they are very high on the "order of engagement". <br>
<br>
To ensure success against most mobs which require a CH order and rampage make sure the CH order clerics do not throw a heal (or stand in agro radius, till ppl engage). They will never get on rampage list, no matter their standing on the hate list.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps somewhat. With some practice you can easily assign one guy to get high on rampage list and take all rampages wiith a dedicated healer. <br>
<br>
Please correct me if any of this info is wrong.<br>
<br>
-Desi of Wraith<br>
